parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A ruptured or failed fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, fires, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
A failed fuel sending unit can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, fuel leaks, and fuel pump failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A failed fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Inadequate or incomplete recall repairs can lead to ongoing fuel leaks, fuel pump failure, and other safety issues.
symptoms: and other symptoms related to the original fuel tank or fuel sending unit failure.
